    "cli.help.dismissNotification": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Usage: coterm dismiss-notification (--id <uuid> | --all-read)\n\nRemove one notification, or remove every already-read notification.\n\nFlags:\n  --id <uuid>           Notification id to remove\n  --all-read            Remove every already-read notification\n  --json                Print JSON\n  --id-format <mode>    refs, uuids, or both"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cli.help.jumpToUnread": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Usage: coterm jump-to-unread\n\nFocus the latest unread notification, matching the Notifications page action.\n\nFlags:\n  --json                Print JSON\n  --id-format <mode>    refs, uuids, or both"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cli.help.markNotificationRead": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Usage: coterm mark-notification-read (--id <uuid> | --workspace <id|ref> [--surface <id|ref>] | --all)\n\nMark notifications read without opening them. Exactly one selector is required.\n\nFlags:\n  --id <uuid>           Mark one notification read\n  --workspace <id|ref>  Mark notifications for a workspace\n  --surface <id|ref>    Narrow --workspace to one surface\n  --all                 Mark every notification read\n  --json                Print JSON\n  --id-format <mode>    refs, uuids, or both"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cli.help.memory": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Usage: coterm memory [flags]\n\nDiagnose coterm app memory separately from recursive terminal child-process RSS.\n\nFlags:\n  --all                         Include all windows (default: current window only)\n  --workspace <id|ref|index>   Limit workspace context for attribution labels\n  --groups <count>              Number of child command groups to show (default: 12)\n  --json                        Structured JSON output\n\nOutput:\n  App footprint is the direct coterm process physical footprint from macOS process accounting.\n  Child RSS is recursive resident memory for descendants of the coterm app process,\n  grouped by command name and attributed back to workspace, pane, and surface when known.\n\nExample:\n  coterm memory\n  coterm memory --groups 20\n  coterm --json memory --all"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cli.help.openNotification": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Usage: coterm open-notification --id <uuid>\n\nFocus the notification's workspace and surface, then mark the row read.\n\nFlags:\n  --id <uuid>           Notification id to open\n  --json                Print JSON\n  --id-format <mode>    refs, uuids, or both"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cli.help.reorderWorkspaces": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Usage: coterm reorder-workspaces --order <id|ref|index>,<id|ref|index>,... [flags]\n\nReorder workspaces within a window as one atomic batch. The comma-separated\norder is the final leading order inside the pinned and unpinned groups;\nunmentioned workspaces keep their relative order after listed peers in the\nsame group.\n\nFlags:\n  --order <refs>                Comma-separated workspace refs to place first\n  --window <id|ref|index>       Window context\n  --dry-run                     Print the resolved final indexes without applying\n\nExample:\n  coterm reorder-workspaces --order workspace:1,workspace:11,workspace:31\n  coterm reorder-workspaces --order workspace:11,workspace:1 --dry-run"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cli.help.setStatus": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Usage: coterm set-status <key> <value> [flags]\n\nSet a sidebar status entry for a workspace. Status entries appear as\npills in the sidebar tab row. Use a unique key so different tools\n(e.g. \"claude_code\", \"build\") can manage their own entries.\n\nFlags:\n  --icon <name>          Icon name (e.g. \"sparkle\", \"hammer\")\n  --color <#hex>         Pill color (e.g. \"#ff9500\")\n  --priority <n>         Sort priority; higher appears first (default: 0)\n  --workspace <id|ref>   Target workspace (default: $COTERM_WORKSPACE_ID)\n\nExample:\n  coterm set-status build \"compiling\" --icon hammer --color \"#ff9500\" --priority 80\n  coterm set-status deploy \"v1.2.3\" --workspace workspace:2"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cli.help.ssh": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Usage: coterm ssh <destination> [flags] [-- <remote-command-args>]\n\nCreate a new workspace, mark it as remote-SSH, and start an SSH session in that workspace.\ncoterm will also establish a local SSH proxy endpoint so browser traffic can egress from the remote host.\n\nFlags:\n  --name <title>          Optional workspace title\n  --port <n>              SSH port\n  --identity <path>       SSH identity file path\n  -A, --forward-agent     Forward the caller's SSH agent; also honors ForwardAgent yes from ssh_config\n  -a, --no-forward-agent  Disable SSH agent forwarding for this workspace\n  --ssh-option <opt>      Extra SSH -o option (repeatable)\n  --window <id|ref|index> Target window for the managed workspace\n  --no-focus              Create workspace without switching to it\n\nExample:\n  coterm ssh dev@my-host\n  coterm ssh dev@my-host --name \"gpu-box\" --port 2222 --identity ~/.ssh/id_ed25519\n  coterm ssh dev@my-host --forward-agent\n  coterm ssh dev@my-host --ssh-option UserKnownHostsFile=/dev/null --ssh-option StrictHostKeyChecking=no"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cli.help.ssh-tmux": {
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Usage: coterm ssh-tmux <destination> [--port <n>] [--identity <path>] [--no-focus]\n\nOpen a dedicated coterm window that mirrors a remote host's tmux sessions over\ntmux control mode (tmux -CC) via SSH: each tmux session becomes a workspace,\neach window a tab, and a multi-pane window a native split. Requires the\n\"Remote tmux\" beta to be enabled in Settings.\n\nIf the host needs interactive authentication (password, host-key confirmation,\nMFA, or a security-key touch), coterm runs ssh inline in this terminal so you can\nauthenticate, then mirrors the sessions over the shared SSH connection. Hosts\nthat authenticate non-interactively (ssh-agent / key in ~/.ssh/config) mirror\nwith no prompt. ~/.ssh/config aliases and their IdentityFile/ProxyJump/Port\nsettings are honored.\n\nFlags:\n  --port <n>          SSH port\n  --identity <path>   SSH identity file path\n  --no-focus          Open the mirror window without activating it\n\nExample:\n  coterm ssh-tmux dev@my-host\n  coterm ssh-tmux my-ssh-alias\n  coterm ssh-tmux dev@my-host --port 2222 --identity ~/.ssh/id_ed25519"
          }
        }
      }
    },
